{{Orphan|date=May 2017}} {{Infobox video game | title = 2XL Fleet Defense | image = File:2XL_Fleet_Defense.jpg | caption = title screen | developer = [[2XL Games]] | publisher = | engine = | released = December 5, 2009 | genre = [[Action game|Action]] | modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]] | platforms = [[iOS]] }} '''''2XL Fleet Defense''''' is an iOS game developed by American studio [[2XL Games]] and released on December 5, 2009.
==Critical reception== TouchArcade gave the game a rating of 70%, writing " Fans of either of the aforementioned craft management games should find Fleet Defense to be a challenging (and enjoyably frustrating) twist on the formula. Fun isn't all about offroad racing, after all."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://toucharcade.com/2009/12/05/2xl-fleet-defense-war-on-the-open-seas/|title='2XL Fleet Defense': War on the Open Seas|date=5 December 2009|website=Toucharcade.com|accessdate=2017-05-17}}</ref> Appspy gave the game 3 out of 5, concluding "If you’re looking for a decent time killer then 2XL Fleet Defense is a good choice but don’t expect too much out of it."<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.appspy.com/review/3683/2xl-fleet-defense|title=2XL Fleet Defense Review|author=Damian Chiappara|date=11 December 2009|website=Appspy.com}}</ref> TheAppEra wrote "My overall impression on Fleet Defense was actually not bad. The game does have replay value and is able to keep you trying to pass level four, but it’s almost nearly impossible afterwards. Yet, I would still recommend it to any true gamer."<ref>{{cite web |url=http://theappera.com/2010/01/19/2xl-fleet-defense-review-2xl-can-do-great-casual-games-as-well/ |title=2XL Fleet Defense Review: 2XL Can Do Great CASUAL Games As Well! |publisher=The Appera |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141006175337/http://theappera.com/2010/01/19/2xl-fleet-defense-review-2xl-can-do-great-casual-games-as-well/ |archivedate=6 October 2014}}</ref>
