'''Tehran International Puppet Theatre Festival''' (est.1989) or '''Mobarak International Puppet Theater Festival''' occurs in [[Tehran]], [[Iran]], about every two years. It features [[puppetry]] acts from around the world.<ref>{{Citation |publisher = Routledge |isbn = 9780415260879 |title = World Encyclopedia of Contemporary Theatre: Asia/Pacific |url = http://openlibrary.org/books/OL7488911M/World_Encyclopedia_of_Contemporary_Theatre |author = Don Rubin et al., eds. |publication-date = 2001 |id = 0415260876 }}</ref> Event organizers include Rahmatollah Mehrabi<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.jamejamonline.ir/en/newstext.aspx?newsnum=100946155583 |title=Mobarak Intl. Puppet Theater Festival kicks off in Tehran |author=Jamejam Inc. |authorlink=Jaam-e Jam (newspaper) |date=August 11, 2008 |work=Jamejam Online |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> and Ardeshir Salehpour.<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.unima.org/uni131_Iran_14Festival.pdf |title=Call for participation from Dramatic Arts Center of Iran |year=2012 |location=Tehran |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref>
Among the participants: * [https://web.archive.org/web/20130602005013/http://dollstheatre.net/ Dolls Theatre], Kolkata, India<ref>{{cite web |url=http://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/city/calcutta-times/City-puppet-theatre-on-an-Iraninan-tour/articleshow/18898946.cms |title=City puppet theatre on an Iraninan tour |author=Sriya Ray Chaudhuri |date=Aug 12, 2002 |work=Times of India |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref><ref>{{cite book |title=Indian Puppets |author1=Sampa Ghosh |author2=Utpal Kumar Banerjee |year=2006 |publisher=Abhinav Publications |location=New Delhi}}</ref> * Yase-e-Tamam, Tehran<ref>{{cite web |url=http://isharapuppet.com/IsharaPuppets/calender.htm |title=Ishara Calendar 2012 |author=Ishara Puppet Theatre Trust |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * [[State Puppet Theatre Varna]], Bulgaria<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.vnpuppet.com/en/festivals |title=State Puppet Theatre Varna |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * Puppetmongers, Canada<ref>{{cite web |url=http://puppetmongers.com/Touring.html |title=Puppetmongers.com |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * Marionettentheater Schloss Schönbrunn, Vienna, Austria<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.marionettentheater.at/portal2.php?id=7&lang=en |title=Marionettentheater Schloss Schönbrunn |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * Magisch Theatertje, Netherlands<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.magisch-theatertje.nl/en/cantos_animata.htm |title=Magisch Theatertje |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * Belarusian Theatre Lialka, Belarus<ref>{{cite web |url=http://lialka.by/eng/p/theater_history/ |title=Belarusian Theatre Lialka |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * Strangeface Theatre Co., Kent, England<ref>{{cite web |url=http://caravanshowcase.org.uk/blog/strangeface-theatre-company-recount-touring-to-iran-in-2010/ |title=Strangeface Theatre Company recount touring to Iran in 2010 |date=February 22, 2012 |work=Caravan |location=UK |accessdate=June 28, 2012}}</ref> * Strings Attached Puppet Theatre, Germany<ref name="ttimes2012">{{c